# Day 13 – S3 Troubleshooting (Access Denied & Bucket Policies)

## Goal
Learn how to troubleshoot S3 permission errors and fix bucket policies.

## Steps
- Created S3 bucket and uploaded file.
- Attached IAM ReadOnly policy.
- Tested delete → AccessDenied error.
- Added bucket policy with delete permission.
- Retested → delete worked.

## Lessons Learned
- AccessDenied usually means missing IAM or bucket policy permissions.
- IAM policies control user actions, bucket policies control resource access.
- Always apply least privilege: only allow needed actions.

